				\begin{document}$$ PS=\frac{ Pqm}{ k\tau}\left[ \ln \left(\frac{I_o\alpha ChlC}{ Pqm}+\sqrt{1+{\left(\frac{I_o\alpha ChlC}{ Pqm}\right)}^2}\right)- \ln \left(\frac{I_o\alpha ChlC}{ Pqm}{e}^{- k\tau}+\sqrt{1+{\left(\frac{I_o\alpha ChlC}{ Pqm}{e}^{- k\tau}\right)}^2}\right)\right] $$\end{document}where α is the photosynthetic efficiency at I = 0, I0 is the surface irradiance, ChlC is the ratio of chlorophyll to carbon, Pqm is the absolute maximum rate of photosynthesis and k is the attenuation factor of the culture and a function of ChlC. The last four are dynamic variables so their values are updated at each timestep to capture photoacclimation effects (see Flynn (2001) for further details of how they are calculated).
